column2: You can release / accept commitments 3 times respectivley at most per day.   To release commitment, players must reach level 15; to accept commitment, players must reach level 30.

Quest Commitment Release Rules:

1. Players of level 26 and above can be released for commitment.

2. Guild Quest (offered by The Statue of Sword) and the quest offered by  can be commited.

3. It costs 1 silver to release quest.

4. 3 quests can be released at most per day. (no matter the quest is finsihed or cancelled)

5. You must accept the quest you need to release before you release it.

6. The commited quest will be marked in the quest list.

7. If you kill the monster required by the commited quest, the killing can be calcualated but you cannot report this quest until its commitment ends.

Quest Commitment & Accept Rules:

1. Players of level 31 and above can accept committed quest.

2. 3 committed quests can be accepted at most per day.  You can only accept one committed quest each time.  (no matter you finish it or not)

3. You can check details before accepting the quests.

4. You need to pay 1 Gold as commission.

   (1) The commission will be sent back to you if you finish the quest within time.

   (2) If you fail to finish the quest, the commission will not be returned to you.

5. You will get system rewards via mail after you've finished the quest.
